Moses parted the Red Sea, and the blood 
that splattered as he ran. The worst for 
us: the hospital, or to the people in 
those condos, getting them all out 
of there and going back. Buses going 
back again, buses leaving out 
New Orleans again. That’s how it 
was. You find it when you’re tearing 
up your life, trying to get into 
the Convention Center, the buses came 
in. Every night. Every 
day they was telling us “The buses 
is coming, the buses is coming.
” The buses passed right there in front 
of us, who knew the storm he sailed in 
